These dates do not reflect the ongoing bookings and reservations of Camp Kulaqua. Please call for availability August 2025 August 29 - September 1, 2025  • Camp Kulaqua Family Camp Retreat Registration is scheduled to open on Monday, March 10 For information & to register: Click here Please remember, ALL attendees must be registered. A $100.00/reservation non-refundable deposit is due upon time of making reservation. Lodging is first come first serve - Remember your room/unit is private, you choose who to share it with. Lodging fees are separate from the per person event fee Event Fee applies to each person. $183.00/person for ages 4 & up. Free to 3 and under Event fee includes; 9 meals (Friday supper-Monday Lunch), all of the programming, camp activities, off-site Ichetucknee tubing trip (first 250 to register), and so much more! Click here for more information on this special event. September 2025 September 5 - 7, 2025  • FL Conference - Fit Together For information & to register: Click here Please remember, ALL attendees must be registered. A $50.00/person non-refundable deposit is due upon time of making reservation. Lodging is first come first serve - Remember your room/unit is private, you choose who to share it with. Lodging fees are separate from the per person event fee Event Fee applies to each person. Overnight/Weekened: $196.00/person for ages 4 & up. Free to 3 and under. Sabbath Only $159.00/person ages 4 & up. Free to 3 and under. October 2025 October 24 - 26, 2025  • FL Conference - Hispanic Men's Convention For information & to register: Click here Please remember, ALL attendees must be registered. A $75.00/person non-refundable deposit is due upon time of making reservation. Lodging is first come first serve - Remember your room/unit is private, you choose who to share it with. Lodging fees are separate from the per person event fee Event Fee applies to each person. October 27 - 30, 2025  • Camp Kulaqua Young at Heart Married attendees - for information & to register: Click here for married attendee registration Single attendees - for information & to register: Click here for single attendee registration Single attendee registration are for those not coming with a spouse. The lodging is gender specific and is a shared lodging option. Please remember, ALL attendees must be registered. A $25.00/person non-refundable deposit is due upon time of making reservation. November 2025 November 27-30, 2025  • FL Conference - Portuguese Campal Registration opens June 9. For information & to register: Click here Please remember, ALL attendees must be registered. Full payment is due upon making a reservation. Lodging is first come first serve - Remember your room/unit is private, you choose who to share it with. Lodging fees are separate from the per person event fee Event Fee applies to each person. Overnight/Entire Event: $173.00/person for ages 8 & up. $161.00/person for ages 4-7. Free to 3 and under. Sabbath Only $59.25/person ages 8 & up. $54.75/person ages 4-7. Free to 3 and under. *The events on this page pertains to events that Camp Kulaqua manages the registration for (i.e. Women's Retreat, Men's Convention, Camp Meeting, NAD e-Huddle, NAD Church Planters BootCamp, Red Zone, Summer Camp, Single Parent Retreat, Family Camp, Fit Together, Young at Heart, HOSA, and Portuguese Camp Meeting) Click here to login to your Camp Kulaqua reservation account /.mainContentWrapper /.contentWrapper /.contentOuterWrapper Get In Touch 23400 NW 212 Ave. | High Springs, FL 32643 Phone: 386.454.1351 (facebook, twitter, Youtube, Vimeo) - they will not all be visible for all sections: 1 - FB+Blog+Vimeo; 2 - FB,Twitter,YT; 3 - FB+Blog; 4 - Nothing.

For a group reservation, please call (386) 454-1351 & press "0" MAY ● MAY 11 - Mother's Day - Mothers enter free with paying attendees ● MAY 18 - Momma Makeup Day - Mothers enter free with paying attendees ● MAY 26 - Memorial Day, Monday JULY ● JULY 13 ● JULY 27 STAY TUNED FOR MORE DATES AND FOLLOW US ON FACEBOOK Pricing ●  $19 per person ●  Children 3 & under are free Times: ●  Opens at 10:00am ●  Closes at 5:30pm Please Note: Due to reoccurring situations with alcohol and glass containers encountered at the Water Park on Community Days, Camp Kulaqua will be carrying out a bag and cooler check to enter the park.  No alcohol or glass containers are permitted on-premises. ●  We request that modest swimsuits be worn. ●  Feel free to bring food and coolers, but no glass containers. ●  Coolers and bags will be checked at entrance ●  No alcohol allowed on premises ●  No profanity is permitted ●  No music via speakers / bluetooth devices to be played. We offer overhead music via our system. We look forward to seeing you and your family at Kulaqua's River Ranch Water Park! /.mainContentWrapper /.contentWrapper /.contentOuterWrapper Get In Touch 23400 NW 212 Ave. | High Springs, FL 32643 Phone: 386.454.1351 (facebook, twitter, Youtube, Vimeo) - they will not all be visible for all sections: 1 - FB+Blog+Vimeo; 2 - FB,Twitter,YT; 3 - FB+Blog; 4 - Nothing.

Camp Kulaqua Retreat and Conference Center was a direct answer to their desires and prayers, and ever since God’s blessings have been evident all around. Our Retreat and Conference Center has grown into one of the largest Seventh-day Adventist Camps in the world and is one of the favorite destinations for Florida Conference churches and events! We also serve many other Christian groups of different denominations, schools and field trips, universities and community programs, as well as other not-for-profit organizations and many more. In this age of technology, our biggest desire is to provide a place where people can come together, enjoy the great outdoors and connect with God through His creation in a much deeper and personal way. Camp Kulaqua's Mission Statement: Camp Kulaqua’s mission is to serve the constituents of the Florida Conference of Seventh-Day Adventists with a friendly and quality camping and retreat facility that sets an atmosphere allowing for the Holy Spirit to touch as many lives as possible. Secondarily, to use Camp Kulaqua as an outreach to non-members who can abide by the policies of the Seventh-Day Adventist Church and the principles of Christianity. May all be to the honor and glory of God. Camp Kulaqua's Vision Statement: Serving Together for Jesus… In His Church In His Community In His Creation Furthering the Kingdom of Christ /.mainContentWrapper /.contentWrapper /.contentOuterWrapper Get In Touch 23400 NW 212 Ave. | High Springs, FL 32643 Phone: 386.454.1351 (facebook, twitter, Youtube, Vimeo) - they will not all be visible for all sections: 1 - FB+Blog+Vimeo; 2 - FB,Twitter,YT; 3 - FB+Blog; 4 - Nothing.
